headline: China's Momenta teams up with Grab on autonomous driving in Southeast Asia
summary: China's autonomous driving startup Momenta ​has entered a ‌strategic partnership with Singapore-based Grab, the ‌companies said on Thursday. Momenta, together with Pony AI and WeRide, is among a rising ⁠number of ‌Chinese self-driving technology firms pursuing overseas expansion as ‍Beijing pushes its companies to dominate the sector globally. Thursday's statement ​said Momenta received an ‌undisclosed amount of strategic investment from Grab.
